Package neureka.devices.file.handles

Class IDXHandle

  • java.lang.Object
    • neureka.devices.file.handles.AbstractFileHandle<IDXHandle,​java.lang.Number>
      • neureka.devices.file.handles.IDXHandle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FileHandle<IDXHandle,​java.lang.Number>, Storage<java.lang.Number>
    public final class IDXHandle
extends AbstractFileHandle<IDXHandle,​java.lang.Number>
    This class is one of many extensions of the AbstractFileHandle which is therefore ultimately an implementation of the FileHandle interface. Like other FileHandle implementations this class represents a file of a given type, in this case it represents a IDX file.

      • store

        public <T extends java.lang.Number> IDXHandle store​(Tsr<T> tensor)
        Description copied from interface: Storage
        Implementations of this method ought to store the value of the given tensor in whatever formant suites the underlying implementation and or final type. Classes like "OpenCLDevice" or "FileDevice" for example are tensor storages.
        Type Parameters:
        T - A valid value type of the tensor which ought to be stored on this device.
        Parameters:
        tensor - The tensor whose data ought to be stored.
        Returns:
        A reference this object to allow for method chaining. (factory pattern)

      • getDataSize

        public int getDataSize()
        Description copied from interface: FileHandle
        This method returns the byte size of the data which is stored in the tensor of the file which is managed by this FileHandle. The underlying datatype of the data within the file does not matter.
        Returns:
        The byte size of the data of the underlying tensor body.

      • getTotalSize

        public int getTotalSize()
        Description copied from interface: FileHandle
        This method returns the number of bytes which are used to store the tensor in the file whose access is being managed by an implementation of th FileHandle interface. Metadata stored inside the file will also be included in this returned size.
        Returns:
        The byte size of all the bytes used to represent the tensor in the file.
